Chavez Family Privacy Policy

Effective Date: 5/16/2023

1. Introduction

This Privacy Policy governs the manner in which Chavez Family collects, uses, maintains, and discloses information collected from users ("User" or "Users") of the Chavez Family mobile application ("App").

2. Personal Information Collection

a. Information You Provide: We may collect personal identification information from Users when they voluntarily provide such information, such as when Users register an account, fill out a form, or interact with the App's features. This may include, but is not limited to, the User's name and email address.

b. Information Automatically Collected: We may collect non-personal identification information about Users whenever they interact with our App. This may include technical information about the User's device, such as the operating system, unique device identifiers, IP address, and mobile network information.

3. How We Use Collected Information

a. Personal Information: We may use the personal information provided by Users for the following purposes:

- To personalize the User experience

b. Non-personal Information: We may use non-personal information collected from Users for analytics purposes, to monitor and analyze trends, to enhance the functionality and performance of the App.

4. Data Retention

We will retain the collected information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes outlined in this Privacy Policy, unless a longer retention period is required or permitted by law.

5. Information Sharing

We do not sell, trade, or rent Users' personal identification information to others.

6. Third-Party Services

We may use third-party service providers to assist us in operating the App and to help us analyze how it is used. These third parties will have access to Users' information only to perform specific tasks on our behalf and are obligated not to disclose or use it for any other purpose.

7. Data Security

We implement appropriate data collection, storage, and processing practices and security measures to protect against unauthorized access, alteration, disclosure, or destruction of Users' personal information, username, password, transaction information, and data stored on our App.

8. Changes to this Privacy Policy

We reserve the right to update this Privacy Policy at any time. Users are encouraged to check this page periodically for any changes. You acknowledge and agree that it is your responsibility to review this Privacy Policy periodically and become aware of modifications.
